{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 65 g butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/70°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place plain flour, wholemeal flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Add 115 g butter and pulse <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/3-4 times<b> until fine breadcrumbs form.","Add apples and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Add maple syrup, eggs and reserved melted butter then stir <b>10-15 sec\/\/speed 3<b> until mixed well.","Add bacon and stir in with spatula.","Line a baking tray with baking paper then tip dough out onto it. Shape into a circle (Ø 12-15 cm), cut circle into 8 wedges and pull apart slightly. Freeze for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 220°C.","Remove tray from freezer. Brush tops of dough with milk and sprinkle with sugar (if using). Bake for 15 minutes (220°C) or until golden.","Leave on tray to cool for 5 minutes before serving warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["180 g unsalted butter, cold, diced","160 g plain flour","160 g wholemeal flour","1 Tbsp baking powder","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground cinnamon","&frac18; tsp ground nutmeg","&frac18; tsp ground cloves","120 g apples, peeled, cored, diced (5 mm)","50 g maple syrup","2 large eggs","3 slices cooked bacon, cut in pieces (1 cm)","50 g milk","Demerara sugar, for sprinkling (optional)"]}],"id":"r282101","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-KXJlMlloySw\/XZadUmjO_QI\/AAAAAAAAgao\/nH8X96j26MItnU82iV86ylsYrYXhNzfDgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8jDDA87v6J8BFmO-.png","title":"Apple and Maple Syrup Bacon Scones","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"14.9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"22.8 g","calories":"1061 kJ \/ 254 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pastry brush, baking tray, baking paper, freezer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Inspired by the classic American pairing of bacon and maple syrup, these sweet and savoury scones will soon become a family favourite. Serve warm from the oven topped with a little butter."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 10m","12 pieces"]}